225 grams King Prawns
180 grams Spaghetti
30 grams Tomato Puree
75 grams Creme Fraiche
50 grams Harissa Paste
28 grams Red Wine Stock Paste
100 grams Baby Spinach
20 grams Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese
1 tsp Sugar
125 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce

Boil a full kettle.
Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium-high heat.
Drain the prawns.
Once hot, fry the prawns, 2-3 mins. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a saucepan with 1/2 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the pasta, 8 mins.

Once the prawns are cooked, stir in the tomato puree, creme fraiche, harissa (add less if you'd prefer things milder), red wine stock paste, sugar and water (see pantry for both).
Bring to the boil then simmer, 3-4 mins.
Add the spinach in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, 1-2 mins.
Stir through the cheese. IMPORTANT: Cook so the prawns are opaque in the middle.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain and add to the sauce. Toss to coat.
Share the pasta between your bowls.
Enjoy!